text.section:
"Carrier" means:
An insurer;
A nonprofit health service plan;
A health maintenance organization; or
Any other person that provides health benefit plans subject to regulation by the State.

section.section:
"Health benefit plan" does not include:
Coverage for accident or disability income insurance;
Coverage issued as a supplement to liability insurance;
Liability insurance, including general liability insurance and automobile liability insurance;
Workers' compensation or similar insurance;
Automobile or property medical payment insurance;
Credit-only insurance;
Coverage for on-site medical clinics;
Dental or vision insurance;
Long-term care insurance or benefits for nursing home care, home health care, community-based care, or any combination of these;
Coverage only for a specified disease or illness;
Hospital indemnity or other fixed indemnity insurance; or
The following benefits if offered as a separate insurance policy:
Medicare supplemental health insurance, as defined in § 1882(g)(1) of the Social Security Act;
Coverage supplemental to the coverage provided under Chapter 55 of Title 10, U.S.C.; or
Similar supplemental coverage provided to coverage under an employer-sponsored plan.

"Health care provider" means:
A person who is licensed, certified, or otherwise authorized under the Health Occupations Article to provide health care in the ordinary course of business or practice of a profession or in an approved education or training program; or
A facility where health care is provided to patients or recipients, including:
A facility, as defined in § 10-101(e) of this article;
A hospital, as defined in § 19-301 of this title;
A related institution, as defined in § 19-301 of this title;
An outpatient clinic;
A freestanding medical facility, as defined in § 19-3A-01 of this title;
An ambulatory surgical facility, as defined in § 19-3B-01 of this title; and
A nursing home, as defined in § 19-1401 of this title.
